thread.title: TV | Aquarius

author: Fiona Flynn
title: TV | Aquarius
text: The first series of this period crime drama that follows the investigation into cult leader Charles Manson comes to an end tonight with a double bill. The first episode sees Detective Hodiak (David Duchovny) continue to pursue the serial killer case as Manson searches for Emma, while the finale sees the Chairman making a breakthrough in the case. The show has already been renewed for a second season, however next time you see David Duchovny in the detective garb will of course be when he returns to his role as Fox Mulder in January. Awahoo.
